   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "For this kind of dateset we don't have to do label encoding instead of the label encoding we do one-hot-encoding for categorical values and standardScalar for numerical values\n",
    "for that we going to separate x (feature) and y (target)"
   ],
   "id": "69c25cfeabcc144b"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2026-03-03T07:25:44.810769Z",
     "start_time": "2026-03-03T07:25:44.802163Z"
    }
   },
   "cell_type": "code",
   "source": [
    "X = df.drop([\"math score\"], axis=1) #remenber here we need to axis=1 for dropping columns\n",
    "y = df[\"math score\"]"
   ],
   "id": "7c4b41ba87e4ceeb",
   "outputs": [],
   "execution_count": 4
  },
  {
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2026-03-03T07:25:46.460371Z",
     "start_time": "2026-03-03T07:25:46.453590Z"
    }
   },
   "cell_type": "code",
   "source": [
    "categorical_cols = X.select_dtypes(include=[\"object\"]).columns\n",
    "numerical_cols = X.select_dtypes(include=[\"int64\", \"float64\"]).columns\n",
    "print(\"categorical:\",  categorical_cols)\n",
    "print(\"numerical_cols\",numerical_cols)"
   ],
   "id": "8734ef9ed26fa5b3",
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "categorical: Index(['gender', 'race/ethnicity', 'parental level of education', 'lunch',\n",
      "       'test preparation course'],\n",
      "      dtype='object')\n",
      "numerical_cols Index(['reading score', 'writing score'], dtype='object')\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "execution_count": 5
  },
  {
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2026-03-03T07:25:48.891609Z",
     "start_time": "2026-03-03T07:25:48.885764Z"
    }
   },
   "cell_type": "code",
   "source": [
    "preprocessor = ColumnTransformer(\n",
    "    transformers=[\n",
    "        (\"numeric\", StandardScaler(), numerical_cols),\n",
    "        (\"categorical\", OneHotEncoder(drop=\"first\"), categorical_cols),\n",
    "    ]\n",
    ")"
   ],
   "id": "8f758f35c7a348f7",
   "outputs": [],
   "execution_count": 6
  },
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "source": [
    "Why drop=\"first\"?\n",
    "To avoid a dummy variable trap (multicollinearity)."
   ],
   "id": "e9a01d57f23b72c"
  },
  {
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2026-03-03T07:25:50.554142Z",
     "start_time": "2026-03-03T07:25:50.549906Z"
    }
   },
   "cell_type": "code",
   "source": [
    "pipeline = Pipeline(steps=[\n",
    "    (\"preprocessor\", preprocessor),\n",
    "    (\"model\", LinearRegression())\n",
    "])"
   ],
   "id": "33688e8b276a3c15",
